SIMPLE: thereat
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thereat
<hw>There*at"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>At
that place; there.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wide is the gate, and broad is the way, that leadeth to
destruction, and many there be which go in <qex>thereat</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Matt. vii. 13.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>At that occurrence or event; on that
account.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Every error is a stain to the beauty of nature; for which cause it
blusheth <qex>thereat</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

